article.headline: Stony Brook 51, Dartmouth 48
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Mitchell Beauford scored 22 points while leading Stony Brook to Tuesday's night's wild 51-48 win over Dartmouth. After Stony Brook went up by as many 15 points early in the second half, Dartmouth chipped steadily away until Leon Pattman's 3- pointer capped an 8-0 run that gave his team a 45-44 lead with 1:58 remaining. It was the first time Dartmouth led all night. A Mike Popoko free throw tied the score for Stony Brook before Beauford scored with 37 seconds left to put Stony Brook (3-10) ahead for good, 47-45. Following another pair of free throws by Popoko, Pattman banked in a 3-pointer with four seconds left to pull Dartmouth (2-11) back within 49-48. But Stony Brook's Henrik Feist closed out the game on a pair of free throws with one second left. Dartmouth got 11 points from Pattman and 10 from Michael Giovacchini.
